issue.body:
Is it somehow possible to fully reset the state of the throttled function?
Maybe to add some parameter to the `cancel` method to handle this case:

```javascript
var throttled = _.throttle(function (param) {
    return param + 1;
}, 1000);

var value = throttled(0); // 1
document.body.textContent = value + '***';

// want to reset the cached value and timeout of `throttled`
// so that it would be possible to immediately call it again 
throttled.cancel();

value = throttled(1); // 1, but want to have 2
document.body.textContent += value;
```

http://jsfiddle.net/ccqgdeaa/1/

